<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}-{3}{y}={0}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{6}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+-{3}{y}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={0}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{0}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{\left(\frac{{{0}-{\left(-{3}{y}\right)}}}{{2}}\right)}+-{6}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{9}}{{2}}\cdot{\left({0}\right)}--\frac{{9}}{{2}}{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{0}-{\left(-{13.5}\right)}{y}+-{6}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{13.5}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}={78}--{0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{13.5}{y}+{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{13.5}+{\left(-{6}\right)}\right)}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{19.5}{y}={78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{78}}{{-{{19.5}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+-{3}{\left(-{4}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}+{\left({12}\right)}={0}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}={0}-{\left({12}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{2}{x}=-{12}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{12}}{{2}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{6}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{6},-{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>